results.title: Secrets of Singapore : Changi Airport
abstracts: Superheroes Danger Dan and Gadget Girl reveal intriguing secrets of Changi Airport, in places like the taxiways, the runways and the apron. They also learn about devices used to screen baggage, and why food tastes like cardboard in a plane!

results.title: Secrets of Singapore : National Gallery
abstracts: This book offers art-related information such as the various art venues in Singapore, tips on how to appreciate art and well-known Singapore artists. Readers can also join Professor Brushie and Curious Canvas in discovering the fascinating facts and history of National Gallery Singapore, such as secret passages, hidden dome and chocolate ceiling.

results.title: Wagga learns about COVID-19
abstracts: This book contains two parts. In the first part, Wagga learns about COVID-19 and how to fight it. In the second part, upset at being unable to go out often, Wagga learns how to cope with his anger and comes up with a "stay at home" plan.

results.title: Golden feathers
abstracts: "Golden feathers" is part of a collection of Jātaka stories, which are used to teach Buddhist values. In this story a mother and her three daughters are presented with a golden feather by a golden swan every day. Soon, however, the mother becomes greedy and wants all the feathers at once. She catches the swan and plucks its feathers. In her hands, the golden feathers turn white and therefore worthless. The swan then grows new feathers, which are also white. Soon the swan flies off, never returning to the family.
